\f1\b0 \cf0 \
So far I've been using 'peace' without actually addressing how 'peace' as a concept is used in the Time Machine For Peace program. Peace and world peace are the most common peace nouns. Let's establish some rules and define terms. This will be essential to understanding in section two and beyond.\
\
This defines the core of the shared language I propose. A glossary and specification is available in appendix[].\
\
First, I refrain from using the phrase 'world peace'. It is too loaded, charged, and elicits imagery of fantasy utopias and kumbaya nonsense. (Kumbaya by the way, originated as a German word meaning 'come from God'.) Instead, we will define 
\f0\b global peace
\f1\b0  as the mature big brother of world peace. Global peace is realistic, messy, chaotic. Global peace is to treat peace on a global scale (species wide), as the 
\f2\i product
\f1\i0  of the global peace system we erect. It is the system's state in any given moment. Likewise, we will add one more version of peace to represent an individual's subjective sense of inner peace. Call this 
\f0\b inner peace
\f1\b0 .\
\
I throw away 
\f2\i peace
\f1\i0 , in general, as it is too vague. Every Human being on the planet has a different understanding of what 
\f2\i peace
\f1\i0  means, so this is way too much to contend with (at least for now). Like 
\f2\i world peace
\f1\i0 , it will be more productive to just leave 
\f2\i peace
\f1\i0  as it is in general use, and avoid it as a general use case whenever possible. For example, I will correlate my 
\f2\i inner peace
\f1\i0  to my sense of 
\f2\i contentment
\f1\i0  but I will 
\f2\i not
\f1\i0  say that 
\f2\i I feel peace
\f1\i0  when what I feel is contentment. The exception to the 
\f2\i peace
\f1\i0  rule is that I will use the noun phrase 
\f2\i peace process
\f1\i0 , which disambiguates 
\f2\i peace
\f1\i0  by specifying that it is whatever goes into creating what people think of as 
\f2\i peace
\f1\i0  in the general sense.\
\
If that isn't enough, this next rule is by far the most irritating aspect of the language choice moving forward. (It absolutely drives people crazy, but this is more a fault of my poor communication skills and their inability to think fluidly.) Bear with me for now. From now on, in place of 
\f2\i peace
\f1\i0  and 
\f2\i world peace
\f1\i0 , we will use the substitutions 
\f2\i piece
\f1\i0  and 
\f2\i world piece
\f1\i0 . Besides 
\f2\i global peace
\f1\i0 , 
\f2\i piece
\f1\i0  and 
\f2\i world piece
\f1\i0  are in fact the most important substitutions we can make. Like 
\f2\i peace
\f1\i0 , the concept of a 
\f2\i piece
\f1\i0  becomes part of the knowledge tree's trunk. Most of this has to do with the fledgling piece-based physics--the qualitative difference physics--that guides this program's efforts. (Section three will dive deep into this, but for now it goes to state that our universe's evolution of real matter and imaginary objects constructs may be best described as a singular blob of pieces. The similarity between 'peace' and 'piece' in the English language may be misfortunate, but then again, there may certainly be a serendipitous link between 'peace' as a concept, and 'piece' as a thing.\
\
